UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1560
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Jerry Carol
2 Edwards, Jr.
3 WHEREAS, Jerry Carol Edwards, Jr., was born on March 4, 1963, in Perry County,
4 Kentucky, to the late Jerry Carol Edwards, Sr., and Georgia Holland Edwards; and
5 WHEREAS, Jerry Carol Edwards, Jr., devoted much of his life to serving his
6 community and earned the respect, trust, and appreciation of the people of Clark County,
7 Kentucky, as Constable for District 5; and
8 WHEREAS, Jerry Carol Edwards, Jr., was a proud member of the Masonic Lodge,
9 exemplifying values of brotherhood and service; and
10 WHEREAS, Jerry Carol Edwards, Jr., worked with both the Wolfe and Perry
11 County Ambulance Services, EMS, and Fire Departments, where he is remembered for
12 his reputation for willingly helping others in need; and
13 WHEREAS, Jerry Carol Edwards, Jr., will be forever remembered and deeply
14 missed by his devoted wife of 28 years, Paula Jean Spicer Edwards; his two sons, Jerry
15 Carol Edwards III and Nicholas Chadwick Edwards; his three sisters, Tammy (Buddy)
16 Gayheart, Sandy (Kevin) Brown, and Susan (Elmer) Grigsby; and numerous extended
17 family members and many dear friends;
18 NOW, THEREFORE,
19 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
20 Kentucky:
21 Section 1. The members of the Senate hereby express their most profound
22 sympathy upon the passing of Jerry Carol Edwards, Jr.
23 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor and loving
24 memory of Jerry Carol Edwards.
25 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
26 Resolution to Senator Greg Elkins for delivery to the family.
